<% content_for :title, "HoneyOps | Privacy Policy" %>
<% content_for :meta_description, "Privacy Policy for HoneyOps, including data categories, legal bases, retention, sharing, and data subject rights." %>

<div class="min-h-screen bg-slate-950 text-slate-100">
  <%= render "main/site_header" %>

  <main>
    <section class="border-b border-slate-900 bg-slate-950 py-16">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-100 sm:text-5xl">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-400">Last updated: March 12, 2026</p>
        <p class="mt-6 text-slate-300">
          This Privacy Policy explains how HoneyOps collects, uses, and protects personal data when you use
          our website, platform, and related services.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="bg-slate-950 py-16">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl space-y-8 px-6 text-slate-300">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">1. Who we are</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            HoneyOps provides a managed honeypot platform for security teams. For account administration and
            customer relationship data, HoneyOps acts as data controller.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">2. Data we collect</h2>
          <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-sm">
            <li>Account and contact data, such as names, company information, and business email addresses.</li>
            <li>Authentication and user management data, including login identifiers and role assignments.</li>
            <li>Service configuration data for honeypots, policies, integrations, and notification channels.</li>
            <li>Security event data generated by honeypot interactions (for example IP, port, protocol, timestamps).</li>
            <li>Operational logs needed to preserve platform security, integrity, and service availability.</li>
            <li>Support communications you send when requesting assistance.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">3. Why we process data</h2>
          <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-sm">
            <li>To provide and operate the HoneyOps platform.</li>
            <li>To authenticate users and enforce role-based access.</li>
            <li>To deliver incident alerts, reporting, and configured notifications.</li>
            <li>To maintain platform reliability and security.</li>
            <li>To provide support and respond to product enquiries.</li>
            <li>To comply with legal and contractual obligations.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">4. Legal bases</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
            Where applicable law requires it (including GDPR), we rely on contractual necessity,
            legitimate interests, and legal obligations as the legal basis for processing.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">5. Sharing and transfers</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
            We do not sell personal data. We may share data with trusted service providers,
            authorized users in your organization, or authorities when legally required.
            If international transfers occur, we apply appropriate safeguards.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">6. Retention</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
            Data is retained only as long as needed for service delivery, security operations,
            and legal compliance requirements.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">7. Your rights</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
            Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have rights to access, correct, delete,
            restrict, or object to processing, and to request portability of eligible data.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">8. Cookies</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
            HoneyOps uses only strictly necessary cookies for secure platform operation.
            See the <%= link_to "Cookie Policy", cookies_path, class: "text-amber-400 hover:underline" %> for details.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">9. Contact</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
            Privacy questions or requests can be sent to
            <a href="mailto:privacy@honeyops.net" class="text-amber-400 hover:underline">privacy@honeyops.net</a>
            or <a href="mailto:info@honeyops.net" class="text-amber-400 hover:underline">info@honeyops.net</a>.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <%= render "main/site_footer" %>
</div>
